5. GEOMETRY.

My compass measures the mighty world, and whatsoever meets the eye in sea or shore; in scales are weighed the masses of sea and the vast earth and the buried realm of Dis. Yet great Heaven has given you, O Chanes, realms too small, and the earth is too narrow for your throne. Democritus, who of old imagined countless worlds, would say they could be ruled with

only you as Jove supreme.
